news.title: Onus for construction site deaths should be on builders too: Activists
news.para: Such incidents keep repeating as the people who hire the workers rarely follow the basic safety norms such as wearing of helmets, harnesses or nets as is mandatory under the law.

news.title: Vadodara: No end to resettlement impasse of Sanjaynagar families
news.para: While the Vadodara Municipal Corporation (VMC) may be wanting to end the impasse regarding the rehabilitation of families ousted from Sanjaynagar in Warasiya and Sahakarnagar in Tandalja, the wait for new houses may get even longer for the 3,269 families.

news.title: Flats handed over in 2014, but infra work not over: GPL Eden Heights residents
news.para: In a letter to the DTCP this week, the society’s RWA alleged that work amounting to Rs 2.4 crore is pending. This also includes repairing security cameras that aren’t functional and malfunctioning boom barriers.

news.title: Real estate sector in Kochi is witnessing a bounce back: Kerala RERA
news.para: Real estate sector in the district is witnessing a bounce back, according to the data with the Kerala Real Estate Regulatory Authority (Rera).

news.title: GOs will help land grabbers: Petitioner to Telangana HC
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Satish Chandra Sharma and Justice Abhinand Kumar Shavili gave the order while resuming its hearing in the PIL filed by senior lecturer Anwar Khan of Hyderabad who questioned the regularisation scheme under government order (GO) MS No 59 issued in December 2014.

news.title: Chennai corporation demolishes 410 buildings on Ramapuram lake
news.para: According to a statement from the corporation, 410 buildings have been razed down so far following a Madras high court direction.

news.title: Existing home sales fall 7.2% in U.S. in February
news.para: With mortgage rates rising above 4% for the first time in nearly three years, sales are likely to slow this year, though that would do little to curb house price inflation. Contracts to buy previously owned houses, a leading indicator of home sales, fell for three straight months through January.

news.title: China's land sales plunged in Jan-Feb though easing measures
news.para: The country's government land sales revenue fell 29.5% on year to 792.2 billion yuan ($124.52 billion) in the first two months of 2022 after a 2.16% increase in December, largely smaller than 1.1236 trillion in the same period in 2021.

news.title: Hyderabad: Owners await payment for acquisition of Old City land
news.para: Owners claim that for the last two years, they have been making rounds of offices, but to no avail. Worse, documents and multiple representations submitted with officials have also not helped them get the money they are entitled to against the land acquisition.

news.title: Kochi metro to begin work on Monday
news.para: KMRL authorities noticed the minor misalignment caused by the settlement of foundations at pillar No 347 a month ago. After the issue came to light, KMRL has imposed speed restriction over the pillar along the route.

news.title: IWG to add over 1,000 locations as firms shift to hybrid work model
news.para: The owner of the Spaces and Regus brands has around 3,500 buildings in more than 120 countries and counts 83% of the Fortune 500 firms among its global customer base. IWG, however, did not provide net addition of its centres for the year, which also takes into account closures if any.

news.title: Mysuru civic body to roll out uniform tax structure for commercial properties on April 1
news.para: The announcement was made on Thursday by M S Shobha, who heads MCC’s standing committee for finance, tax and appeal.

news.title: No plans to sell government land as part of asset monetization: Karnataka CM
news.para: The chief minister’s clarification came as response to leader of opposition BK Hariprasad’s concern that the government may end up selling prime properties belonging to the public sector undertakings including NGEF and Mysore Lamps Factory, which are under liquidation, as the receipts are not up to the expected level.

news.title: Puravankara arm Provident Housing lines up over Rs 3,500-crore expansion plan
news.para: After a lull in the second quarter of 2021 due to a resurgence in the Covid-19 pandemic and restrictions imposed by various state governments, sales gained momentum during the third quarter as the economy picked up, supported by aggressive vaccination drives.

news.title: KKR to buy Japan's Mitsubishi Corp-UBS Realty for $2 billion
news.para: KKR will buy MC-UBSR from Mitsubishi Corp and UBS Asset Management. MC-UBSR was founded in 2000 as a joint venture between the two companies, and is currently one of the largest real estate asset managers in Japan with 1.7 trillion yen in assets under management.
